This is the Manual for the AI022 Harmonic Mixer you can purchase it by going to:
https://aisynthesis.com/product/ai106-west-coast-eurorack-mixer/.
1. About the AI106 West Coast Mixer
The AI106 West Coast Mixer is a discrete mixer using no ICs. As gain increases harmonics and
analog warmth are added. As gain increases more, distortion and phasing is added, creating new
waveforms from old ones.
The AI106 takes inspiration from the legendary but primitive mixers used in 1960s synthesizers
built on the West Coast of the United States, but updates it for eurorack and allows for user
customization of the circuit.

2. AI106 Controls
1. Mono Inputs. These inputs
accept mono audio or voltage
signals.
2. Mix Out. This is the primary
voltage output. Just like the
vintage 1960s mixers, the
output is inverted.
4. Input Volume. The position
of these knobs control the
volume of each input. These
knobs are passive attenuators.
As volume increases more
harmonic distortion is added.
5. Master Volume. The position
of this knob controls the
volume of audio and or voltage
of the Mix Out. As volume
increases more harmonic
distortion is added.
3. Power
The AI106 uses a shrouded header to prevent the cable being plugged in the wrong way. The unit
draws 12 mA on the positive rail, and 0 mA on the negative side.
